text: Gaithersburg, officially the City of Gaithersburg, is a city in Montgomery County, Maryland. At the time of the 2020 U.S. Census, Gaithersburg had a population of 69,657. It is the third largest incorporated city in the state, behind Baltimore and Frederick. Gaithersburg was incorporated as a town in 1878 and as a city in 1968. ==References== Category:Cities in Montgomery County, Maryland Category:1878 establishments in the United States Category:1870s establishments in Maryland Category:1968 establishments in the United States Category:20th-century establishments in Maryland
